## Current Architecture Map

```text
YAML recipes (game_data/assets/*.yaml)
  → game_data: definitions.rs → compile.rs → registry.rs (typed, hashed via sha2)
  → game_bevy: config_init.rs / load.rs → ConfigRegistryResource
      ↓
terrain_generation: recipe.rs (RecipeOp graph) + params.rs / island_params.rs
  → island_atlas.rs (2D aligned fields: elevation_regional, elevation_local,
    bathymetry, island_mask, flow_*, river_mask, cliff/beach/soil, biome…)
    built by footprint → coast → erosion → hydrology → river → carving → slope
  → surface_height.rs (analytic coastal surface)
  → DensitySource / RecipeDensitySource (3D signed density; negative = solid)
      ↓
voxel_core: ChunkCoord/WorldCell/WorldSample (coords.rs),
  TerrainChunk 17³ corner samples (terrain_chunk.rs), density_ops.rs (CSG)
      ↓
terrain_meshing: surface_nets.rs → TerrainMeshData (+ bake.rs, material.rs, blend.rs)
      ↓
game_bevy/terrain: pipeline.rs (dispatch/poll density + mesh jobs on
  AsyncComputeTaskPool, chained Update systems) → mesh_convert.rs (cell_size scaling)
  → material.rs/atlas_runtime.rs (shader inputs) → avian3d colliders
  → residency.rs (density/render/physics radii), edits.rs (persistent edits)
      ↓
environment: biomes.rs, biome_context.rs, surface.rs (ChunkSurfaceResolver),
  materials.rs → per-vertex material classification during meshing
```

Density convention: **negative = solid** (`density_ops.rs`: `plane_density = y - height`, `union = min`, `subtract = max(solid, -cavity)`), which matches the doc's expected convention. Vertical axis is Y. Chunks are 16³ cells / 17³ samples, nominally 1 m cells.

